                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 21: The countrys foreign exchange reserves declined $4.56 billion to $282.79 billion for the week ended August 13 from $287.35 billion the previous week because of a heavy dent in foreign currency assets. Foreign currency assets tanked $4.49 billion to $256.59 billion from the previous weeks $261.07 billion, the RBI said in its weekly data. Gold remained unchanged at $19.27 billion, while special drawing rights and reserve position in the IMF slid marginally.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 21: Greaves Cotton Ltd has posted a revenue of Rs 1,347.21 crore for the financial year ended June 30, 2010 against Rs 1,040.80 crore last year. Profit after tax stood at Rs 117.97 crore against Rs 56 crore last year. The company has declared a dividend of Rs 7.5 per share.                                                                                                                          
